---
import { HEAD } from "../styles/constants";

const stats = [
  { num: "~16-23 MB", label: "download" },
  { num: "~60 MB", label: "installed" },
  { num: "0", label: "runtime deps" },
  { num: "0", label: "compiled native code" },
];
---

<section class="section-border reveal pt-10 pb-2">
  <div class="text-center">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The whole thing</p>
    <h2 class={HEAD}>
      ~16–23 MB. Yes, 
      <span
        class="italic text-accent-text"
        style="font-family:var(--font-serif);"
      >
        all of it.
      </span>
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted">
      Electron asks for 150 MB+ before it's done anything. Bunmaska is the
      download you won't notice and the app you can't hear running.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-12 space-y-5 px-4 sm:px-12 lg:px-32">
    <div>
      <div class="mb-2 flex items-baseline justify-between">
        <span class="text-sm text-text-muted">A minimal Electron app</span>
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-text-faint">150 MB+</span>
      </div>
      <div class="h-2.5 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-full bg-bg-muted">
        <div class="h-full w-full rounded-full bg-border-strong"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="mb-2 flex items-baseline justify-between">
        <span class="text-sm font-medium text-text"
          >The same app, on Bunmaska</span
        >
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-accent-text">~16-23 MB</span>
      </div>
      <div class="h-2.5 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-full bg-bg-muted">
        <div class="h-full rounded-full bg-accent" style="width:13%;"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-center text-sm text-text-faint">
      Same app. One bundles a whole browser; the other just doesn't.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div
    class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-2 gap-px overflow-hidden border border-border bg-border md:grid-cols-4"
  >
    {
      stats.map((s) => (
        <div class="bg-bg px-5 py-9 text-center">
          <div class="whitespace-nowrap text-[1.5rem] font-semibold tracking-tight">
            {s.num}
          </div>
          <div class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-text-muted">{s.label}</div>
        </div>
      ))
    }
  </div>

  <p class="mx-auto mt-5 max-w-2xl text-center text-xs text-text-faint">
    That's macOS and Linux, which render on the system's own WebKit - nothing to
    bundle. Windows has no system WebKit, so it ships a from-source WinCairo engine
    (heavier, and shared across apps via the engine store).
  </p>
</section>
